      <hedline>
        <hl1>JAPAN TRADE SURPLUS NARROWS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Miki Tanikawa</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Tanikawa, Miki</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Japan's trade surplus declines in July as economy shows signs of life; trade surplus falls 19.3 percent, to 1 trillion yen, from year-earlier period while Japan's surplus with US declines 13.8 percent, to 620.8 billion yen (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Japan's trade surplus declined as the economy showed signs of life. The Ministry of Finance said the country's trade surplus in July fell 19.3 percent, to 1 trillion yen, from the corresponding month last year while Japan's surplus with the United States, its biggest trading partner, declined 13.8 percent, to 620.8 billion yen. Economists said the narrowing trade surplus reflected Japan's growing appetite to consume.</p>
        <p>Miki Tanikawa (NYT)</p>
      </block>
